<br>
1. Invis vs. animals doesn't work, neither does gather shadows, or superior camoflague.  This is from the 2 druids and the necro that helped.  That and I was camo'd more than a few times.  Wolf form doesnt help either.<br>
<br>
2. When I did it, the best option is to have a cleric get DA and DB up, and pop on DA and kite the sharks away while the wizard hops in and grabs the wand and gates/swims out.<br>
If the first attempt is failed, remind the cleric that the sharks are still agro, wait for DA or DB tor reload, and have him just step in the water further away from the wand.  The sharks will instantly agro on the cleric and will swim after him/her.  If they /q or log, they clear the agro and have to start all over again.<br>
<br>
3. However, the cleric I had needed sleep so I had to call in a necromancer friend.  He just popped on harmshield and feared the sharks while I swam in grabbed the wand and safely swam out.  Its the same basic concept.  The only reason the cleric option didnt work was because I couldnt find the wand on the ground.  You will need Endure Breath of an FBE (or DMF).<br>
<br>
The gobs in Oasis are indifferent to wolf-form.  Frankly I wouldn't do this quest solo, make some friends.  for me it was easy because I planned this a good month in advance, and had all the help I would need lined up (being a bard primarily looking for a new occupation, this proposed the biggest challenge I couold find that would hold my interest).  I got the wands in 3 days.  The toughest part is just finding the rods.  <br>
<br>
The 2 hardest to find are the qeynos catacombs, and the Everfrost wand.  I suggest getting a map or exact locs because these can become dangerous if you take a wrong turn (miragul is in the caverns that holds the everfrost wand, so a wrong turn may leave you at his feet).  I spent a good hour lost in the Qatacombs before getting a map.  After that it was easy.<br>
<br>
The most aggrevating wand (besides the erud's xing) is the Lake Rathtear wand by a long run.  The tunnel is hard to find since its underwater, and, a VERY dark tunnel.  Especially for an erudite like myself.  To ruin the surprise its on the backside of the 3 spawn Aviak Island.<br>
<br>
The easiest ones are in Unrest, DC, and Neriak (depending on race).  They are wide in the open and withe the right type of invis very easy to get.<br>
<br>
Like I said though, I was lucky to have the help I did, but it can be done with preparation.  You just gotta understand that the easiest ones are usually not easy at all, while the ones you dread are quite easy.  For instance, the Lguk rod.  I did this one as soon as I culd get a IVU and a TP.  Just ask is someone is camping the hand room (and it almost always is camped) just walk in, grab it and walk out.<br>
<br>
- aaeandar vie<br>
