<br>
Azia:  The sharks are PCaggro.  This means that they won't con indifferent even if they can't see you.  (I am not completely sure they can see invisible, but I swam right next to them invisibly without getting attacked.)  The best strategy is to swim straight down and then straight back up.  The sharks circle the bottom and will stay there unless chasing you.<br>
<br>
Bezia:  Buy a SoW or a Sow potion for this one if you are too low.  You should be able to easily escape the skeletons and gate once you've gained enough distance.<br>
<br>
Caza:  The easiest way to find the entrance is to use the head bobbing technique.  You get your eyes just even with the waterline and you can see clearly long distances.  Note that the piece is on TOP of the tower.  The goblins here can't see invis but the others can so don't go mucking around the lower area.  When you approach come in from behind the direction the goblins are facing when possible.  This will make it harder for them to notice you when you go visible after taking the piece.<br>
<br>
Dena:  This piece is unguarded and easy to retrieve.  Regular invis should work.<br>
<br>
Ena:  This is the toughest of the lot.  Chances are invis to undead will run out before you get to your destination so there's really only two reliable ways to do this: either get a high level escort or buy several invis undead potions.  It also helps to do this piece on a weekend when guk is full and monster population is down.  Note:  To those who have never seen this room it is a high vertical chamber that is essentially a water tube.  You must swim up the tube to get to where the piece is.<br>
<br>
Fana:  Like caza the piece is on the very top area and the goblins can't see invis.    Approach wisely and you can escape unscathed.<br>
<br>
Geza:  This piece is unguarded and easy to retrieve.  Regular invis should work.<br>
<br>
Heda:  Invis and dive.  The shark is fairly low level, but if you are trying this at low level you may want to have a friend distract the shark.  Suicide pets work nicely as the shark can't come out of the water after you once he's done with the pet.<br>
<br>
Izah:  Gate after getting this one.  The safest area is probably the water.  Trying to get back to land will only get you killed.<br>
<br>
Jaka:  Unguarded.  If you can't get this piece I wouldn't suggest starting the quest yet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udinaedinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dinaedinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/19/00 8:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How I got the Eruds x-ing rod</span><hr size=1> At level 46 I died a few times (those of you who have died in level 46 will sympathise with me on this one...) trying to get this rod.<br>
