 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uradcliffe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Radcliffe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/21/00 9:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How I got the Eruds x-ing rod</span><hr size=1> I levitated, invised and walked to the loc and swam down and got it - never saw a shark. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uienilae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ienilae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/21/00 10:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How I got the Eruds x-ing rod</span><hr size=1> I got this staff after they implemented the change to the sharks. This is about the best way I can tell you to do it since the Sharks saw thru both invise. Go out get a lvl50+War someone with massive hp get 2-3 clerics and a good enchanter have the war go down Fully buffed and have him agro all 6sharks maybe 7 dont remember. But soon as he has agro have clerics start CH him so he can stay alive Enchanter starts mezing the sharks while you go down and pick up your rod soon as you get rod gate to shore and port them all out. This worked real well for me. And from what they said was great exp killing those sharks for them. Works out for all. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/24/00 1:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bah!  Don't need no stinking other Classes....</span><hr size=1> I did the Tarton's Wheel innumerable times. Whenever I couldn't find a group, as it yielded so much exp., I would go do it after L 29 when I first did it.  BTW the exp comes from turning in the Staff and the jewel.  Also gives BetaNeutral faction.<br>
<br>
NO invis or camo works all the time.  No aid of spell other than ours is of much use except a method of Endure Breathe and Sow (which is, as always, LIFE, as it allows backwards movement underwater).  <br>
<br>
The sharks are bad.  Very bad.  I am 55 and I don't think I would want to fight them.  However, there is a way to avoid them.  The sharks are in a triangle of spawn points.  <br>
<br>
From the beach, face the wreck.  Enter the water a bit to the left of the leftmost part of the wreck.  Swim out along the bottom.  Just past the ship, the bottom drops out.  Go straight down.  Stop.  Look for the sharks.  One is to your right 10 degrees or so off in the gloom, rather near the drop-off just past the right end of the wreck, but on the deeper bottom at your level.  The rod is about 45 degrees out from you to the right.<br>
<br>
The sharks swim a circuit of their triangle.  I recommend waiting a few minutes and seeing the movement so you realize exactly where they go.  The one closest swims out past the rod to his next point.  Wait till he is somewhat past the rod, nearly to his next point.  Then, swim to the rod, grab it, and swim back - don't put in inventory till you are clear.  MOVE.  NO DAWDLING.  DON'T GET NEAR HIM!  The next shark will be moving into the shore position that the other vacated by the time you have the rod and are moving back out of aggro range.<br>
<br>
Alternately, the sharks sometimes move differently.  The one that you can see past the rod on the left sometimes moves to his next station before the closer in one moves (I think this happens when a player or you have distrupted them).  In this case, swim straight out from your watch point to level with the rod (which is now due right).  Look to see if the other shark is coming from the shore area.  If it's not, you can reach the rod from this angle without triggering its aggro range - as long as it does not move.<br>
<br>
If you do this fast, the next shark is not in range.  If you are hit by a shark, Yonder and Gate.   Sometimes the magic works, and sometimes it doesn't.   Do remember though, that Yonder might fling you a LONG way or a short.  I always have a loc hot key and hit it while Gate is cycling.  I always write the loc down incase I lockup while LOADING, PLEASE WAIT.  If the sharks get me, I come back with Levitation to the point and /corpse back to shore on the surface, there being no Z range to worry about.  I try to sell a few batwings to the Vendor so that they are there (unless someone buys or her memory of items is full).  I drop a couple on the beach just before I enter the water too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxaxia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaxia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/25/00 11:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: staff of the wheel, rod in eruds x-ing</span><hr size=1> I have 8 of the 10 rods now, with only the Hand Room and Everfrost ones left.  For me, the Oasis and Lake Rathe ones were harder than the Erud's Crossing one.  And here's why.<br>
<br>
I am 22 now (was 23 before this, sigh) and am doing the quest with Pause, who is 16.  I am indebted to Stillnight, a 51 wizardess who has helped us along the way and provided support.<br>
<br>
LAKE RATHE<br>
<br>
That LONG tunnel on the west side of the 3-spawn island was an omen for me.  I guess it's a test to make us all into brave little wizards and wizardesses.  I just have to say, I was scared to death!  Being Erudites, we started by casting Heatsight, used a waterstone, and Invised (regular).  Waterstones are definitely a must.  They are summoned from a 20th level magician and are NO RENT.  I heard wolf-from does not aggro the DW goblins, but we didn't have that luxury (and I'm not positive it works anyway).<br>
<br>
After we both found the tower, I actually entered it (stupid, stupid, stupid), swam up to the top floor, and instantly died.  As I lay there in a pool of blood, I actually SAW the rod beside me, but didn't have time to pick it up.  Pause stayed down for a couple of minutes and then gated back WITH ROD!  He is such an awesome wizard!<br>
<br>
This was his method.  There are 3 goblins on the top floor of the tower with an NPC Deep (she is non-aggro).  Con each goblin to see which scowl.  For us, one of them did, and this is the one that will attack if you go in tower.  The goblins have a VERY small aggro radius.  Swim above the window that has the rod closest to it.   It's the window with the two chests next to it; the rod is between the chests and very close to the window.  Float down to window but make sure you don't land on the ledge or you will aggro.  Keep clicking on the rod until you get it.  I had to swim up and float down about 6 or 7 times before I could click on rod.  BE PATIENT.  If invis breaks just swim away and re-cast.  Endure breathing lasts a LONG LONG LONG time.  Once you get the rod, swim away from tower, put rod in inventory, and Gate.<br>
<br>
I actually died twice here, but it can be done without a death, without wolf-form and without an uberguild.<br>
<br>
Stillnight retrieved both of my corpses and got the waterstones from a friend.<br>
<br>
OASIS<br>
<br>
Exactly the same setup as Lake Rathe, except there's no tunnel and the rod is unreachable from outside the window.  In Rathe, the rod is located very near the window; here the rod is almost exactly in the center of the floor.  I was attacked by a goblin and kamakazied it into the tower.  Fortunately, I was able to pick up the rod before I died.  When I did my corpse recovery, the rod was in my invertory.  Yippie!<br>
<br>
ERUD'S CROSSING<br>
<br>
I guess we both got lucky with this one.  Pause and I did this alone.  Read the Ice Comet spoiler here, under the rod for Erud's Crossing.  Also, what Mandos said is true.<br>
<br>
I cast Heatsight, Waterstone, and regular Invis (but this broke during and wasn't even needed).  Face directly west, with the ship on your right side.  Swim out (with belly on the ocean floor the WHOLE time - very important) until you hit the second coordinate of the rod (-2340).  You will be south of the rod now.  Face north, and go VERY slowly, inching your way to the rod.  Do not panic and more importantly: keep your LOC at -2340!!  I came to rod, picked it up, did NOT put in inventory, did a 180, and swam for about 10 seconds, then Gated.<br>
<br>
I never saw one shark or anything else for that matter.  It was nighttime (very dark under there!) and maybe they were all sleeping, dunno.  Pause then did the same thing and got his rod.  No sharks at all.<br>
<br>
Maybe this was pure luck, but I followed Graffe's spoiler to a &quot;T.&quot;  Thank you, Graffe! <p>Xaxia<BR>Erudite Wizardess<BR>22nd Season</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ezelenerinyes>EzelenErinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/25/00 12:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bah!  Don't need no stinking other Classes....</span><hr size=1> HAHAHAHAHAHA I had no clue that there were these sharks in the water...i hopped off the boat from Erudin at lvl 28 and swam right to the wand. Sure it wasn't smart but i didnt see one shark on the way there....although dont think i'll be swimming there any time soon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><strong>Ezelen Erinyes</strong> - Wizard of Tarew Marr<BR>
